This paper deals with deep neural networks and their Hessian matrices, which are commonly studied in the field of machine learning. The paper discusses the structure of the derivative of the logits with respect to the parameters of the model, which is a topic related to optimization and training of neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
